{"cursor":"10726","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In mathematics, especially group theory, the elements of any group may be\npartitioned into 'conjugacy classes'; members of the same conjugacy class share\nmany properties, and study of conjugacy classes of non-abelian groups reveals\nmany important features of their structure. In all abelian\ngroups every conjugacy class is a set containing one element (singleton set).\n\nFunctions that are constant for members of the same conjugacy class are called\nclass functions.\n","linknr":168,"url":"Conjugation_(group_theory)","recorded":1362565167,"links":19,"instances":["mathematics","mathematics","group_theory","mathematics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Group theory"],"headings":["Definition","Examples","Properties","Conjugacy class equation","Conjugacy of subgroups and general subsets","Conjugacy as group action","Geometric interpretation","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/7/2/772d08a1575d3a088fffbdcb24fed41c.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/e/7/e/e7e8784769adf2907f64f315769091dc.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["group","mathematics"],["singleton","mathematics"],["function","mathematics"],["order","group_theory"]],"members":["group","function","order","singleton"],"related":["Mathematics","Group_theory","Group_(mathematics)","Partition_of_a_set","Abelian_group","Singleton_(mathematics)","Function_(mathematics)","Class_function","Linear_algebra","Matrix_similarity","Equivalence_relation","Equivalence_class","If_and_only_if","Disjoint_sets","Symmetric_group","Permutation","Integer_partition","Cycle_notation","Abelian_group","Order_(group_theory)","Center_of_a_group","Subgroup","Index_of_a_subgroup","Orbit-stabilizer_theorem","Finite_group","Coset","Centralizer","Index_of_a_subg